  "genre": "hiphop",
  "mode": "sleep",
  "mixStrategy": "This sleep-mode hip hop arrangement in Cm uses a i \u2192 iv \u2192 bVI \u2192 bVII progression (Cm \u2192 Fm \u2192 Ab \u2192 Bb) cycling every ~15 seconds (3 cycles over 45s). FREQUENCY SEPARATION: The Synth Bass (GM 38) anchors the sub-bass region (MIDI 36-48, 65-130Hz) with long 5-8s sustained root notes that provide a warm, dark 808-style foundation. The Warm Pad (GM 89) fills the mid frequencies (MIDI 48-67, 130Hz-600Hz) with slow-moving minor chord voicings that shift gently with each chord change, creating harmonic body. The Vibraphone melody (GM 11) floats in the upper register (MIDI 67-79, 600Hz-2kHz) with sparse, bell-like phrases that use chord tones on strong beats and pentatonic passing tones between. ENERGY ARC: The piece is divided into 6 segments (~7.5s each). Segments 1&6 (0-7.5s, 37.5-45s) are the quietest \u2014 fewest notes, lowest velocities (25-40). Segments 2&5 (7.5-15s, 30-37.5s) add slightly more motion. Segments 3&4 (15-30s) represent the gentle peak with marginally more melodic movement and slightly higher velocities, but never exceeding the sleep ceiling. COHESION: All three tracks change chords simultaneously at 0s (Cm), 3.75s (Fm), 7.5s (Ab), 11.25s (Bb), and repeat. Bass always plays the root. Pad voicings always include root-b3-5th (or root-4th-b7 for Fm). Melody targets chord tones (C, Eb, G for Cm; F, Ab, C for Fm; Ab, C, Eb for Ab; Bb, D, F for Bb) on downbeats. NO drums \u2014 pure ambient warmth. The overall effect is a dark, enveloping cloud of sound that breathes slowly, perfect for sleep.",
